+ Forest and other wooded land managed (either wholly or in combination) for timber production, recreation and amenity, conservation and environmental uses e.g.Forestry Commission and Forest Enterprise plantations, woodland in official grant schemes, woodland certified to UK Woodland Assurance Scheme (UKWASS) standards.

+ Woodland used for seasonal grazing and foraging by livestock, and where timber is used on-farm, e.g. as a source of fencing material, or as a short-term crop in its own right (e.g. coppiced woodland for energy crops purposes).

+ Felled woodland and land cultivated for afforestation.

